    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="196"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the Ambassador in
                        the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HWA2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d196fn1">Sent to the United States Naval
                        Attaché, Moscow, via Navy channels. A copy was sent to the Department of
                        State for its information.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">operational priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-08">8 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName> from the
                    President.</p>
                <p>My 041707,<note n="2" xml:id="d196fn2">Telegram of November 4, 1943; see <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_151">p. 151</ref>, footnote
                        1.</note> your 06100.<note n="3" xml:id="d196fn3">Telegram of November 6,
                        1943, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_158">p. 158</ref>. The
                        date-time group was garbled.</note>
                </p>
                <p>You are hereby authorized to attach our agreement regarding Turkey to the
                    protocol with the following change.</p>
                <p>Change the words “Commanders responsible” to the words “Combined Chiefs of
                        Staff.”<note n="4" xml:id="d196fn4">See <persName corresp="#p_CC2"
                            >Churchill</persName>’s telegram 493, November 6, 1943, to <persName
                            corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>,
                            <ref target="#pg_156">p. 156</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
